bodily_process.n.01.defn: an organic process that takes place in the body

activity.n.04.defn: (chemistry) the capacity of a substance to take part in a chemical reaction

natural_process.n.01.defn: a process existing in or produced by nature (rather than by the intent of human beings)

expl: the level of activity declines with age
activeness.n.02.defn: the trait of being active; moving or acting rapidly and energetically
